<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="367" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1837,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1837,1862]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Description.</emphasis>
Body large, robust, with numerous conspicuous pits on surface of vertex, face, pronotum, mesonotum, basal 
<number box="[365,375,1873,1897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[387,401,1873,1897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" value="3.0">3</number>
of forewing and abdomen. Head in dorsal view with anterior margin rounded, parallel to posterior margin, slightly narrower than pronotum. Face relatively short, anteclypeus narrow. Forewing with first and fourth apical cells broad, second and third cells narrow, fourth cell approximately same length as third, AA and AP veins absent. 
<collectingCountry box="[345,401,1981,2005]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing without RA vein.
</paragraph>
